[SN]TITLE[SN]
How are you celebrating the Women's World Cup?

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The 2015 Women's World Cup is under way and concludes with the final on Sunday, 5 July in Vancouver, Canada. Who are you supporting?

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The expanded edition of the football competition will feature 24 teams for the first time and could reach up to a billion TV viewers around the world.
Eight sides make their World Cup debuts. Germany and the United States start as favourites as they seek to win a third global title.
